FBIS4-52995 "dreas095_c_94026" FBIS-EAS-94-095 Daily Report 14 May 1994 North Korea Kim Il-song Sends Message to Palestinian President Kim Il-song Sends Message to Palestinian President SK1405112394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1049 GMT 14 May 94 SK1405112394 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea on May 14 sent a message of solidarity to Yasir 'Arafat, president of the state of Palestine and chairman of the Executive Committee of the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO), on the occasion of the "week of support to the Palestinian people's struggle". President Kim Il-song said the Palestinian people are now vigorously struggling to put an end to Israeli occupation and restore their lawful national rights and it is fully supported by the progressive people of the world. Wishing the Palestinian president and people success in the work for a political solution to the Palestinian issue and promotion of the Mideast peace process, he expressed the belief that the friendship and unity and bonds of solidarity between the peoples of Korea and Palestine will steadily grow stronger and develop.
